OL,3,CGovernment u-turn sees taxpayer cover
OL,4,C#121,000 for event overspend
OL,6,FIn a letter from Chief Minister Lyndon
OL,7,FFarnham and Deputy Morel, addressed to
OL,8,Fthe Chief Officer at the Department of
OL,9,Fthe Economy, the Government adds: "We
OL,10,Fwould ask that any future grants to
OL,11,Fany organiser of the Battle of Flowers
OL,12,Fevent are made with this funding in
OL,13,Fmind, accounted for accordingly and
OL,14,Fdeducted from future grants to the
OL,15,Fevent.
