OL,3,CGovernment u-turn sees taxpayer cover
OL,4,C#121,000 for event overspend
OL,6,F"It is unfortunate that, despite the
OL,7,Fefforts of the new organisers and the
OL,8,Fgrant funding already provided by the
OL,9,FDepartment for the Economy, the
OL,10,Fsuccess of the event should be
OL,11,Fimperilled due to ongoing challenges
OL,12,Fin resolving the 2024 overspend."
OL,14,FSome islanders believe money from the
OL,15,Fpublic purse could be better allocated
OL,16,Felsewhere.
